Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.59,1:52:31.96,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Keep out! Keep out!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.96,1:52:33.46,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Keep out! Keep out!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.46,1:52:35.00,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Keep out!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.00,1:52:36.50,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Assholes.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.50,1:52:39.44,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Gay Men's Health Crisis.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.44,1:52:41.00,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Thrush is a fungus, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.00,1:52:42.50,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Can you tell him that we'll be picketing there
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.50,1:52:44.04,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,and not afraid of arrest or police brutality.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.04,1:52:45.21,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- Gay Men's Health Crisis. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.21,1:52:47.58,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,The mayor has four more hours before we carry out
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.58,1:52:49.98,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,our threats of civil disobedience if he doesn't meet with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.98,1:52:52.18,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Tommy got the call yesterday, Ned.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.79,1:52:57.05,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.05,1:52:58.79,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You see, it works!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.79,1:53:02.43,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- When? When? - Only two can go to the meeting, Ned.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.86,1:53:05.73,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- When? - Tommy's executive director.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.73,1:53:08.90,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.90,1:53:10.93,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- I polled the fucking board, Ned. - I wrote that letter
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.93,1:53:12.97,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,to the mayor. That meeting is mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.97,1:53:15.84,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I am going to go and represent this organization
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.84,1:53:18.51,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,that I have spent every minute of my life fighting for
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.51,1:53:20.48,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,and that was started in my living room
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.48,1:53:22.34,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,or I quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.38,1:53:30.29,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You'd let me quit?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.56,1:53:41.36,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,The board asked me to read this out loud to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.36,1:53:43.86,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- Read what? - A letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:50.61,1:53:52.61,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Go on, read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.88,1:53:58.11,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,"We are circulating this letter widely among people
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.11,1:54:01.58,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,of judgment and good sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.58,1:54:06.32,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You are on a colossal ego trip we must curtail.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.32,1:54:09.29,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,To manipulate fear as you have done repeatedly
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.29,1:54:13.13,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,is to us, sheer barbarism.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.13,1:54:15.79,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,To exploit the deaths of gay men as you have done
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.80,1:54:19.20,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,on television and in publications all over America
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.20,1:54:22.74,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,is to us, an act of vandalism.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.77,1:54:27.14,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,And after years of liberation
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.14,1:54:30.74,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,you helped make sex dirty again for us...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.74,1:54:34.31,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,terrible and forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.31,1:54:37.12,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,We are more angry at you
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.12,1:54:40.29,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,than ever in our lives toward anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.29,1:54:44.02,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,We think you want to lead us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.02,1:54:45.82,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.82,1:54:49.29,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,we do not want you to lead us.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.70,1:54:59.14,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,In accordance with our bylaws as drawn up by Weeks, Frankel, Levinstein
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.14,1:55:01.74,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Mr. Ned Weeks is hereby removed
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.74,1:55:05.54,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,as a director of Gay Men's Health Crisis.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.54,1:55:09.58,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,We beg that you leave us quietly
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.58,1:55:13.72,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,and not destroy us and what good work we manage
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.72,1:55:16.35,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,despite your disapproval.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.35,1:55:19.02,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Effective immediately."
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.61,1:55:43.11,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Ned.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.11,1:55:46.38,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,The executive director isn't on the board, you know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.38,1:55:48.02,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I don't have a vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.02,1:55:49.49,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,What could... what could I have done?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.49,1:55:51.89,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- You didn't support me. - That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.89,1:55:53.32,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You're all nothing but undertakers.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.32,1:55:55.06,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,This whole organization is a funeral parlor.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.06,1:55:57.83,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Ned... - All you do is take care of the dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.83,1:56:00.10,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Who's fighting so the living can go on living?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.10,1:56:02.20,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Who's fighting for my Felix?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.20,1:56:05.27,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Tommy. We need you upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.41,1:56:13.21,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I belong to a culture that includes Marcel Proust
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.21,1:56:16.61,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Walt Whitman, Tennessee Williams, Alexander the Great
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.61,1:56:19.45,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,so many popes and cardinals you wouldn't believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.45,1:56:22.52,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Mr. Green Beret, did you know that it was an openly gay Englishman
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.52,1:56:25.15,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,who's responsible for winning World War II?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.15,1:56:28.76,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,His name's Alan Turing and he cracked the Germans' Enigma code.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.76,1:56:30.66,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,After the war was over, he committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.66,1:56:33.66,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,because he was so hounded for being gay.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.66,1:56:36.33,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Why didn't they teach any of that in schools?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.33,1:56:40.70,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,A gay man is responsible for winning World War II!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.00,1:56:43.77,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,If they did, maybe he wouldn't have killed himself
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.77,1:56:47.04,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,and you wouldn't be so terrified of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.41,1:56:53.45,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,That's how I want to be remembered.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.45,1:56:55.52,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,As one of the men who won the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:59.45,1:57:03.56,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Bruce, I know that I am an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.56,1:57:07.13,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,But please don't shut me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.63,1:57:46.07,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.95,1:58:02.18,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Your brother and I are lovers.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.88,1:58:06.59,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I'm dying and I need to make a will.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.12,1:58:11.19,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- Please. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.64,1:58:27.97,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I want to leave everything to Ned.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.64,1:58:34.98,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- How's my brother? - Well, he blames himself for everything
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.98,1:58:39.98,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,from my dying to the state of the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:39.99,1:58:43.35,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,All that plus you two still not talking.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.86,1:58:48.36,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You must be as stubborn as he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.43,1:58:52.13,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I'll call him right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.13,1:58:55.30,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Do. He's at home packing.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.30,1:58:58.87,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,We're going to Yale in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:58.87,1:59:01.97,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,For Gay Week.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.97,1:59:03.81,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,He says he can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.98,1:59:09.11,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,He tried to kill himself there when he was a freshman.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.92,1:59:16.49,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I haven't much...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.26,1:59:20.86,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,except for a beautiful piece of land
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.86,1:59:23.76,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,on the Cape in Wellfleet.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.10,1:59:27.66,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Ned doesn't know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:27.66,1:59:29.60,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,It was to have been a surprise
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.60,1:59:31.94,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,for when we lived there together
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.94,1:59:36.14,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,riding away happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:36.14,1:59:39.54,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I also have an insurance policy
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.54,1:59:42.85,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,uh... with the "Times." I'm a reporter...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.85,1:59:44.58,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,for "The New York Times."
Dialogue: 0,1:59:44.58,1:59:48.45,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,It's meant to come to my next of kin.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.45,1:59:50.09,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I'm afraid they might not give it to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:50.09,1:59:52.22,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Well, if he's listed as a beneficiary, they must.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:52.22,1:59:54.66,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You're smarter than that. Don't be so naive.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.66,1:59:58.39,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I assure you, I will fight to make sure that they do.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.63,2:00:05.00,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I was hoping you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.27,2:00:14.31,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Felix...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.11,2:00:18.71,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I wish we'd met sooner.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.68,2:01:16.77,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I should be wearing something white
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.78,2:01:19.02,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You are, honey.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:19.77,2:01:21.81,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,It should... it should be something
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.81,2:01:27.21,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Perry Ellis ran up for me personally.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:34.09,2:01:36.22,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Ned?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:40.73,2:01:43.56,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,You find a way to fight again.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:45.40,2:01:47.40,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:52.14,2:01:55.47,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:55.47,2:01:57.68,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:05.89,2:02:08.65,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Emma. Emma...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:08.65,2:02:12.39,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Could we... could we start now, please?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:21.43,2:02:24.33,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,We are gathered here in the sight of God
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.34,2:02:27.54,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,to join together these two men.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:27.54,2:02:29.77,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,They love each other
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.77,2:02:31.98,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,very much and...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.98,2:02:37.15,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,want to be married in the presence of their family and friends
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.25,2:02:43.59,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I see no objection.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.59,2:02:45.82,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,Do you, Felix Turner
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.82,2:02:50.36,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- take Ned Weeks..." - Alexander. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:53.46,2:02:58.87,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,- To be your... - My great true love.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.47,2:03:06.94,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:09.98,2:03:13.48,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I do. I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:14.88,2:03:16.85,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:16.85,2:03:18.45,Default1,NTP,0,0,0,,I do.
